=Description=

Greg Cassel:

"This document is an overview of digital networking models for peer-to-peer (p2p) digital media signaling, storage, co-editing, and community-developed resource description frameworks (RDFs).  My main goal here is to help enhance the ability of all persons and peer groups to communicate and organize effectively.  

This document prioritizes personal agency and freedom of expression, information and interaction.  However, I note my strong belief that more effective and sustainably distributed peer-to-peer networking will strongly favor inclusive community-building, and commons principles, over the violent, confusing, coercive and deceptive forces which often thrive in large-scale organizational forms.     "



